title: Here's what happened to Star Wars’ Jar Jar Binks, the franchise's most hated character of all time
text:
Here's what happened to Star Wars’ Jar Jar Binks, the franchise's most hated character of all time You’ll never believe what he’s up to now... Share 'Where are they now?' Star Wars character Jar Jar Binks was slated when he made his first appearance in the film franchise back in 1999 with The Phantom Menace. 
Despite a blink and you’ll miss it cameo at a funeral in Episode III: Revenge Of The Sith, clumsy Gungan Jar Jar had pretty much disappeared off the face of the galaxy. 
But now, a new Star Wars novel has revealed his whereabouts and what he’s up to. 
Often regarded by fans as the one of the worst Star Wars characters to ever grace the screen, Jar Jar inadvertently wreaked havoc in the galaxy. Jar Jar Binks is back The Gungan, pictured here with an Ewok, is now a clown (Photo: Lucasfilm) 
In Attack Of The Clones, he inadvertently helped create the Empire by proposing the war powers act when he was a Galactic Senator, a move which weakened the Republic. 
And in Star Wars Aftermath: Empire’s End by Chuck Wendig, time has not been so kind to Jar Jar. 
The book takes place between Return Of The Jedi and The Force Awakens, episodes six and seven, and is set on the planet of Naboo. Jar Jar Binks lives - and he's still on Naboo Jar Jar made his debut in Star Wars Episode I - The Phantom Menace (Photo: Fox) 
A refugee boy named Mapo meets a clown there, who turns out to be actual Jar Jar. He’s now got a career performing for street kids and trying to make them laugh. 
Jar Jar tells the boy, “Meesa Jar Jar”, before popping his eyes out to try and raise a laugh, and admits he screwed up a bit - hence his new profession as a clown. 
"Jar Jar makin some uh-oh mistakens," he says. "Desa hisen Naboo tink I help the uh-oh Empire." 
Indeed.
